<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Refers to the distribution of this species in the lands of the Maya.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
(holotype). Carapace length 2.0; abdomen length 1.7. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Carapace</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">7</figureCitation>
) with long fovea; anterior eye row approx. as wide as carapace, and wider than posterior row. PME small, displaced medially to lie behind medial edge of ALE. Ocular area medium brown under alcohol and darker around eyes, dusted with dull brown and tan scales that are oriented concentrically around the unusually large PLE. Thoracic area brown, with paler medial longitudinal band, and paler spots just above each of the leg coxae. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Clypeus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) narrow and with a few scattered whitish hairs and scales. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Chelicerae</emphasis>
vertical and relatively small. Four small but distinct teeth on retromargin of chelicerae (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); promargin not observed (on the specimen from Guatemala, three promarginal teeth). 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Palp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Figs 1-4</figureCitation>
) with embolus arising on prolateral side, narrowing abruptly, then bending directly to the retrolateral, where it meets a large sclerotized projection (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">p</emphasis>
in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) that envelops it so completely that the terminal third of the embolus is most easily seen as a dark line within the projection; the tip of the embolus rests within the tip of the projection. The projection consists of a plate at the distal edge of the bulb, which then narrows before swelling and curving to a point that projects ventrally. (Regarding its homology to the conductor in 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lapsias" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Lapsias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see comments below.) Median apophysis distinct (separated from the tegulum by a membrane) but relatively small, almost hidden by the sclerotized projection. Cymbium with proximal prolateral conical projection. Retrolateral tibial apophysis a short flange (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) whose ventral edge extends proximally and forms a round pocket facing retrolateral side. Patella with two retrolateral apophyses, the larger one being hooked. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">11</figureCitation>
) pale honey-coloured, darkening to nearly black on distal half of femora, and with broad darker annuli on tibiae and metatarsi. First tibia macrosetae as follows: three pairs of ventral, two to three anterior lateral, two posterior lateral, and one dorsal. First metatarsus macrosetae as follows: two ventral pairs, two anterior lateral, and two posterior lateral. Fourth legs distinctly longest; leg formula 4132. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Amilaps mayana, sp. nov, male holotype 1 - 4 palp 1 ventral view 2 prolateral view 3 ventral view 4 retrolateral view 5 face 6, 7 carapace, dorsal view 8 body in alcohol 9 posterior ventral view of chelicera showing four retromarginal teeth 10, 11 living specimen. Abbreviations: e embolus, s spermophore, ma median apophysis, p sclerotized projection serving as conductor. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (1); 1.0 mm (6, 8)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/357962" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.891.38563.figures1-11">10</figureCitation>
) brown above, with paler undulating medial longitudinal pale band.
</paragraph>
