<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="natural history">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
My field notes for the holotype indicate it was found on a limestone rock face, and the back of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="vial’s">vial's</normalizedToken>
label says &quot;on limestone cliff face on forested slope&quot;. Both the holotype from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
and the male from Guatemala (according to its locality) were associated with caves. The holotype was not in the cave, but on a cliff near the cave.
</paragraph>
